                  <decoDesc>
                     <summary>Classical scene of departure for Hades. An angel (female) is standing to the right of (behind) a seated male figure (presumably the deceased). She holds him by the elbow with her right hand and in her left raised hand she holds an hourglass. She has her hair braided in the back of her head and wears loose hanging drapery / chiton-style. The seated male figure has his draped legs turned sideways to the left of the relief and his nude torso turned almost full front, while looking back at the angel. In his lap is an upright standing lyre, which he supports with his right hand and in his left hand, which hangs down by his side he holds a wreath. At the foot of his seat, below his left hand is a cornucopia and another wreath. All in relief on the S face.</summary>
